Patient: I'm not sure how much water I should be drinking?

Healthcare Educator: Limit your fluid intake to less than 2 liters a day to avoid straining your heart.

Patient: What about coffee and tea? I enjoy those.

Healthcare Educator: Coffee and tea count towards your fluid limit. Try to limit those and drink more water.

Patient: But doesn't water taste boring? 

Healthcare Educator: You can try flavored water or add fresh fruit to make it more enjoyable.

Patient: What if I can't stick to this limit?

Healthcare Educator: It's okay, make gradual changes. Involve your family in helping you keep track.

Patient: Will this really help my heart?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, limiting fluid and reducing sodium can improve your heart health and quality of life.